Musician Ghost: What was that? 
Musician Ghost: Sorry, my hearing isn't as good as it used to be. 
Musician Ghost: Honestly, I thought dying would fix my bad ear, but that ringing in my right ear is annoying as ever.
Musician Ghost: At first, I thought it was just fatigue... maybe my late nights of practicing were getting to me. But, over time, the noise kept getting worse, reverberating into my passions.
Musician Ghost: It drove me crazy not knowing whether my performances were in the wrong key, and every practice session fell flat.
Musician Ghost: It's been a while since I've put on a performance, but I'd like to think I'm a good inspiration away from getting back to my peak.
